{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":468,"text":"I'm here to talk to you about how globalized we are,"},{"time":4999,"text":"how globalized we aren't,"},{"time":7507,"text":"and why it's important to actually be accurate"},{"time":11051,"text":"in making those kinds of assessments."},{"time":13832,"text":"And the leading point of view on this, whether measured"},{"time":17572,"text":"by number of books sold, mentions in media,"},{"time":21763,"text":"or surveys that I've run with groups ranging from"},{"time":24979,"text":"my students to delegates to the World Trade Organization,"},{"time":29056,"text":"is this view that national borders"},{"time":32170,"text":"really don't matter very much anymore,"},{"time":35723,"text":"cross-border integration is close to complete,"},{"time":39779,"text":"and we live in one world."},{"time":42074,"text":"And what's interesting about this view"},{"time":44306,"text":"is, again, it's a view that's held by pro-globalizers"},{"time":47900,"text":"like Tom Friedman, from whose book this quote is obviously excerpted,"},{"time":52674,"text":"but it's also held by anti-globalizers, who see this giant"},{"time":56600,"text":"globalization tsunami that's about to wreck all our lives"},{"time":61491,"text":"if it hasn't already done so."}]},{"cues":[{"time":64375,"text":"The other thing I would add is that this is not a new view."},{"time":68399,"text":"I'm a little bit of an amateur historian, so I've spent"},{"time":72110,"text":"some time going back, trying to see the first mention"},{"time":76091,"text":"of this kind of thing. And the best, earliest quote"},{"time":79810,"text":"that I could find was one from David Livingstone,"},{"time":83654,"text":"writing in the 1850s about how the railroad, the steam ship,"},{"time":89699,"text":"and the telegraph were integrating East Africa perfectly"},{"time":94166,"text":"with the rest of the world."},{"time":97537,"text":"Now clearly, David Livingstone"},{"time":99717,"text":"was a little bit ahead of his time,"},{"time":102737,"text":"but it does seem useful to ask ourselves,"},{"time":106280,"text":"\"Just how global are we?\""},{"time":108376,"text":"before we think about where we go from here."}]},{"cues":[{"time":111079,"text":"So the best way I've found of trying to get people"},{"time":115617,"text":"to take seriously the idea that the world may not be flat,"},{"time":120266,"text":"may not even be close to flat, is with some data."},{"time":124281,"text":"So one of the things I've been doing over the last few years"},{"time":127660,"text":"is really compiling data on things that could either happen"},{"time":131627,"text":"within national borders or across national borders,"},{"time":135782,"text":"and I've looked at the cross-border component"},{"time":139285,"text":"as a percentage of the total."},{"time":141698,"text":"I'm not going to present all the data that I have here today,"},{"time":145663,"text":"but let me just give you a few data points."},{"time":149269,"text":"I'm going to talk a little bit about one kind of information flow,"},{"time":153603,"text":"one kind of flow of people, one kind of flow of capital,"},{"time":158471,"text":"and, of course, trade in products and services."}]},{"cues":[{"time":161952,"text":"So let's start off with plain old telephone service."},{"time":166531,"text":"Of all the voice-calling minutes in the world last year,"},{"time":171624,"text":"what percentage do you think were accounted for"},{"time":176272,"text":"by cross-border phone calls?"},{"time":178597,"text":"Pick a percentage in your own mind."},{"time":182673,"text":"The answer turns out to be two percent."},{"time":185768,"text":"If you include Internet telephony, you might be able"},{"time":189906,"text":"to push this number up to six or seven percent,"},{"time":193333,"text":"but it's nowhere near what people tend to estimate."}]},{"cues":[{"time":197990,"text":"Or let's turn to people moving across borders."},{"time":201735,"text":"One particular thing we might look at, in terms of"},{"time":204952,"text":"long-term flows of people, is what percentage"},{"time":208679,"text":"of the world's population is accounted for"},{"time":212191,"text":"by first-generation immigrants?"},{"time":215199,"text":"Again, please pick a percentage."},{"time":219494,"text":"Turns out to be a little bit higher."},{"time":221919,"text":"It's actually about three percent."}]},{"cues":[{"time":224986,"text":"Or think of investment. Take all the real investment"},{"time":229857,"text":"that went on in the world in 2010."},{"time":233025,"text":"What percentage of that was accounted for"},{"time":235881,"text":"by foreign direct investment?"},{"time":239818,"text":"Not quite ten percent."}]},{"cues":[{"time":243185,"text":"And then finally, the one statistic"},{"time":245824,"text":"that I suspect many of the people in this room have seen:"},{"time":249001,"text":"the export-to-GDP ratio."},{"time":251729,"text":"If you look at the official statistics, they typically indicate"},{"time":255498,"text":"a little bit above 30 percent."},{"time":258057,"text":"However, there's a big problem with the official statistics,"},{"time":263146,"text":"in that if, for instance, a Japanese component supplier"},{"time":268077,"text":"ships something to China to be put into an iPod,"},{"time":271689,"text":"and then the iPod gets shipped to the U.S.,"},{"time":274490,"text":"that component ends up getting counted multiple times."},{"time":278327,"text":"So nobody knows how bad this bias"},{"time":281096,"text":"with the official statistics actually is, so I thought I would"},{"time":284883,"text":"ask the person who's spearheading the effort"},{"time":287467,"text":"to generate data on this, Pascal Lamy,"},{"time":290732,"text":"the Director of the World Trade Organization,"},{"time":293244,"text":"what his best guess would be"},{"time":295571,"text":"of exports as a percentage of GDP,"},{"time":298746,"text":"without the double- and triple-counting,"},{"time":301169,"text":"and it's actually probably a bit under 20 percent, rather than"},{"time":305703,"text":"the 30 percent-plus numbers that we're talking about."}]},{"cues":[{"time":309472,"text":"So it's very clear that if you look at these numbers"},{"time":313655,"text":"or all the other numbers that I talk about in my book,"},{"time":317223,"text":"\"World 3.0,\" that we're very, very far from"},{"time":321610,"text":"the no-border effect benchmark, which would imply"},{"time":325664,"text":"internationalization levels of the order of 85, 90, 95 percent."},{"time":332567,"text":"So clearly, apocalyptically-minded authors"},{"time":336175,"text":"have overstated the case."},{"time":339135,"text":"But it's not just the apocalyptics, as I think of them,"},{"time":343327,"text":"who are prone to this kind of overstatement."},{"time":346552,"text":"I've also spent some time surveying audiences"},{"time":349949,"text":"in different parts of the world"},{"time":351947,"text":"on what they actually guess these numbers to be."},{"time":356007,"text":"Let me share with you the results of a survey"},{"time":359076,"text":"that Harvard Business Review was kind enough to run"},{"time":362415,"text":"of its readership as to what people's guesses"},{"time":365935,"text":"along these dimensions actually were."}]},{"cues":[{"time":370350,"text":"So a couple of observations stand out for me from this slide."},{"time":376285,"text":"First of all, there is a suggestion of some error."},{"time":381200,"text":"Okay. (Laughter)"},{"time":384003,"text":"Second, these are pretty large errors. For four quantities"},{"time":389476,"text":"whose average value is less than 10 percent,"},{"time":392455,"text":"you have people guessing three, four times that level."},{"time":396557,"text":"Even though I'm an economist, I find that"},{"time":399645,"text":"a pretty large error."},{"time":402049,"text":"And third, this is not just confined to the readers"},{"time":405911,"text":"of the Harvard Business Review."},{"time":407871,"text":"I've run several dozen such surveys in different parts"},{"time":411269,"text":"of the world, and in all cases except one,"},{"time":414619,"text":"where a group actually underestimated"},{"time":417491,"text":"the trade-to-GDP ratio, people have this tendency"},{"time":421803,"text":"towards overestimation, and so I thought it important"},{"time":424962,"text":"to give a name to this, and that's what I refer to"},{"time":428267,"text":"as globaloney, the difference between the dark blue bars"},{"time":432844,"text":"and the light gray bars."}]},{"cues":[{"time":435851,"text":"Especially because, I suspect, some of you may still be"},{"time":439987,"text":"a little bit skeptical of the claims, I think it's important"},{"time":444179,"text":"to just spend a little bit of time thinking about"},{"time":447443,"text":"why we might be prone to globaloney."},{"time":451202,"text":"A couple of different reasons come to mind."},{"time":454045,"text":"First of all, there's a real dearth of data in the debate."},{"time":458347,"text":"Let me give you an example. When I first published"},{"time":461528,"text":"some of these data a few years ago"},{"time":464124,"text":"in a magazine called Foreign Policy,"},{"time":466661,"text":"one of the people who wrote in, not entirely in agreement,"},{"time":470231,"text":"was Tom Friedman. And since my article was titled"},{"time":474186,"text":"\"Why the World Isn't Flat,\" that wasn't too surprising. (Laughter)"},{"time":479096,"text":"What was very surprising to me was Tom's critique,"},{"time":483377,"text":"which was, \"Ghemawat's data are narrow.\""},{"time":488315,"text":"And this caused me to scratch my head, because"},{"time":491334,"text":"as I went back through his several-hundred-page book,"},{"time":494471,"text":"I couldn't find a single figure, chart, table,"},{"time":499104,"text":"reference or footnote."},{"time":501832,"text":"So my point is, I haven't presented a lot of data here"},{"time":506439,"text":"to convince you that I'm right, but I would urge you"},{"time":509831,"text":"to go away and look for your own data"},{"time":512816,"text":"to try and actually assess whether some of these"},{"time":516304,"text":"hand-me-down insights that we've been bombarded with"},{"time":520665,"text":"actually are correct."},{"time":522577,"text":"So dearth of data in the debate is one reason."}]},{"cues":[{"time":526109,"text":"A second reason has to do with peer pressure."},{"time":530024,"text":"I remember, I decided to write my"},{"time":533205,"text":"\"Why the World Isn't Flat\" article, because"},{"time":535830,"text":"I was being interviewed on TV in Mumbai,"},{"time":539019,"text":"and the interviewer's first question to me was,"},{"time":542694,"text":"\"Professor Ghemawat, why do you still believe"},{"time":546645,"text":"that the world is round?\" And I started laughing,"},{"time":550825,"text":"because I hadn't come across that formulation before. (Laughter)"},{"time":554598,"text":"And as I was laughing, I was thinking,"},{"time":556937,"text":"I really need a more coherent response, especially"},{"time":559824,"text":"on national TV. I'd better write something about this. (Laughter)"},{"time":563934,"text":"But what I can't quite capture for you"},{"time":566903,"text":"was the pity and disbelief"},{"time":569503,"text":"with which the interviewer asked her question."},{"time":572981,"text":"The perspective was, here is this poor professor."},{"time":577321,"text":"He's clearly been in a cave for the last 20,000 years."},{"time":582007,"text":"He really has no idea"},{"time":584655,"text":"as to what's actually going on in the world."},{"time":587613,"text":"So try this out with your friends and acquaintances,"},{"time":591086,"text":"if you like. You'll find that it's very cool"},{"time":594527,"text":"to talk about the world being one, etc."},{"time":597815,"text":"If you raise questions about that formulation,"},{"time":601118,"text":"you really are considered a bit of an antique."}]},{"cues":[{"time":605015,"text":"And then the final reason, which I mention,"},{"time":608469,"text":"especially to a TED audience, with some trepidation,"},{"time":612182,"text":"has to do with what I call \"techno-trances.\""},{"time":615527,"text":"If you listen to techno music for long periods of time,"},{"time":619054,"text":"it does things to your brainwave activity. (Laughter)"},{"time":622406,"text":"Something similar seems to happen"},{"time":625864,"text":"with exaggerated conceptions of how technology"},{"time":631174,"text":"is going to overpower in the very immediate run"},{"time":635343,"text":"all cultural barriers, all political barriers,"},{"time":638676,"text":"all geographic barriers, because at this point"},{"time":642269,"text":"I know you aren't allowed to ask me questions,"},{"time":644853,"text":"but when I get to this point in my lecture with my students,"},{"time":647826,"text":"hands go up, and people ask me,"},{"time":650590,"text":"\"Yeah, but what about Facebook?\""},{"time":654069,"text":"And I got this question often enough that I thought"},{"time":656682,"text":"I'd better do some research on Facebook."},{"time":659430,"text":"Because, in some sense, it's the ideal kind of technology"},{"time":663150,"text":"to think about. Theoretically, it makes it"},{"time":666819,"text":"as easy to form friendships halfway around the world"},{"time":670197,"text":"as opposed to right next door."},{"time":673199,"text":"What percentage of people's friends on Facebook"},{"time":679285,"text":"are actually located in countries other than where"},{"time":682405,"text":"people we're analyzing are based?"},{"time":685678,"text":"The answer is probably somewhere between"},{"time":689028,"text":"10 to 15 percent."},{"time":691901,"text":"Non-negligible, so we don't live in an entirely local"},{"time":695712,"text":"or national world, but very, very far from the 95 percent level"},{"time":700719,"text":"that you would expect, and the reason's very simple."},{"time":704125,"text":"We don't, or I hope we don't, form friendships at random"},{"time":708117,"text":"on Facebook. The technology is overlaid"},{"time":712939,"text":"on a pre-existing matrix of relationships that we have,"},{"time":717674,"text":"and those relationships are what the technology"},{"time":720742,"text":"doesn't quite displace. Those relationships are why"},{"time":723973,"text":"we get far fewer than 95 percent of our friends"},{"time":728017,"text":"being located in countries other than where we are."}]},{"cues":[{"time":731825,"text":"So does all this matter? Or is globaloney"},{"time":737306,"text":"just a harmless way of getting people to pay more attention"},{"time":742718,"text":"to globalization-related issues?"},{"time":745430,"text":"I want to suggest that actually,"},{"time":747637,"text":"globaloney can be very harmful to your health."},{"time":752207,"text":"First of all, recognizing that the glass"},{"time":755359,"text":"is only 10 to 20 percent full is critical to seeing"},{"time":759815,"text":"that there might be potential for additional gains"},{"time":763199,"text":"from additional integration,"},{"time":765230,"text":"whereas if we thought we were already there,"},{"time":768074,"text":"there would be no particular point to pushing harder."},{"time":771498,"text":"It's a little bit like, we wouldn't be having a conference"},{"time":774710,"text":"on radical openness if we already thought we were totally open"},{"time":778891,"text":"to all the kinds of influences that are being talked about"},{"time":782223,"text":"at this conference."},{"time":783638,"text":"So being accurate about how limited globalization levels are"},{"time":788428,"text":"is critical to even being able to notice"},{"time":791487,"text":"that there might be room for something more,"},{"time":795166,"text":"something that would contribute further to global welfare."}]},{"cues":[{"time":799134,"text":"Which brings me to my second point."},{"time":801966,"text":"Avoiding overstatement is also very helpful"},{"time":806189,"text":"because it reduces and in some cases even reverses"},{"time":810984,"text":"some of the fears that people have about globalization."},{"time":815789,"text":"So I actually spend most of my \"World 3.0\" book"},{"time":819174,"text":"working through a litany of market failures and fears"},{"time":823718,"text":"that people have that they worry globalization is going to exacerbate."},{"time":828858,"text":"I'm obviously not going to be able to do that for you today,"},{"time":832526,"text":"so let me just present to you two headlines"},{"time":835794,"text":"as an illustration of what I have in mind."},{"time":839075,"text":"Think of France and the current debate about immigration."},{"time":843391,"text":"When you ask people in France what percentage"},{"time":846623,"text":"of the French population is immigrants,"},{"time":848836,"text":"the answer is about 24 percent. That's their guess."},{"time":853336,"text":"Maybe realizing that the number is just eight percent"},{"time":857966,"text":"might help cool some of the superheated rhetoric"},{"time":862380,"text":"that we see around the immigration issue."},{"time":865718,"text":"Or to take an even more striking example,"},{"time":869862,"text":"when the Chicago Council on Foreign Relations"},{"time":872039,"text":"did a survey of Americans, asking them to guess"},{"time":875386,"text":"what percentage of the federal budget went to foreign aid,"},{"time":879613,"text":"the guess was 30 percent, which is"},{"time":883294,"text":"slightly in excess of the actual level — (\"actually about ... 1%\") (Laughter) —"},{"time":888654,"text":"of U.S. governmental commitments to federal aid."},{"time":892028,"text":"The reassuring thing about this particular survey was,"},{"time":895435,"text":"when it was pointed out to people how far"},{"time":898116,"text":"their estimates were from the actual data,"},{"time":901325,"text":"some of them — not all of them — seemed to become"},{"time":904420,"text":"more willing to consider increases in foreign aid."}]},{"cues":[{"time":908407,"text":"So foreign aid is actually a great way"},{"time":911531,"text":"of sort of wrapping up here, because"},{"time":914725,"text":"if you think about it, what I've been talking about today"},{"time":917813,"text":"is this notion -- very uncontroversial amongst economists --"},{"time":921902,"text":"that most things are very home-biased."},{"time":924884,"text":"\"Foreign aid is the most aid to poor people,\""},{"time":928109,"text":"is about the most home-biased thing you can find."},{"time":931832,"text":"If you look at the OECD countries and how much"},{"time":934870,"text":"they spend per domestic poor person,"},{"time":938012,"text":"and compare it with how much they spend"},{"time":940264,"text":"per poor person in poor countries,"},{"time":944436,"text":"the ratio — Branko Milanovic at the World Bank did the calculations —"},{"time":948708,"text":"turns out to be about 30,000 to one."},{"time":953384,"text":"Now of course, some of us, if we truly are cosmopolitan,"},{"time":959580,"text":"would like to see that ratio being brought down"},{"time":962749,"text":"to one-is-to-one."},{"time":964981,"text":"I'd like to make the suggestion that we don't need to aim"},{"time":968372,"text":"for that to make substantial progress from where we are."},{"time":972533,"text":"If we simply brought that ratio down to 15,000 to one,"},{"time":977600,"text":"we would be meeting those aid targets that were agreed"},{"time":980970,"text":"at the Rio Summit 20 years ago that the summit"},{"time":984487,"text":"that ended last week made no further progress on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":988349,"text":"So in summary, while radical openness is great,"},{"time":992154,"text":"given how closed we are,"},{"time":994167,"text":"even incremental openness could make things"},{"time":997141,"text":"dramatically better. Thank you very much. (Applause)"},{"time":1000772,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}